  "instructions": [
    "Heat the beurre-monte in the lacquerware bowl over medium heat.",
    "Add the onion and cook until it is softened and lightly browned.",
    "Add the garlic and ginger and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the lamb and cook until it is browned on all sides.",
    "Add the cumin, smoked paprika, and cayenne pepper and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the rose water, salt, and black pepper and stir to combine.",
    "Bring the mixture to a boil, then reduce the heat to low and simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.",
    "Remove the lid and simmer for an additional 30 minutes, or until the lamb is tender.",
    "Serve the tagine hot, garnished with fresh herbs if desired."
  ],
